The evidence with the title 'Triple talaq in India - Wikipedia ' says Triple Talaq, also known as talaq-e-biddat, instant divorce and talaq-e- mughallazah (irrevocable divorce), is a form of Islamic divorce which has been used by Muslims in India , especially adherents of Hanafi Sunni Islamic schools of jurisprudence . It allows any Muslim man to legally divorce his wife by stating the word talaq  ... The man did not need to cite any cause for the divorce and the wife need not  ... 
